"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/576412","Department for Education","false","2016-09-13","<p>In-school organisation, such as streaming or setting, is a matter for individual schools, and data is not collected or held by the Department on this matter.</p><p> </p>","Bognor Regis and Littlehampton","Nick Gibb",,"2016-09-13T15:11:58.18Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/576412/answer","Biography information for Nick Gibb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/576412/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/576412/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2016-09-05","Schools: Teaching Methods","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, whether her Department holds data on the (a) use and (b) prevalence of setting and streaming in schools in England.","false","Biography information for John Glen","Salisbury","John Glen","44947"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/576413","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2016-09-08","<p>Exit from the European Union presents us with an opportunity to improve the way waters in the United Kingdom’s Exclusive Economic Zone are managed. No decisions have yet been taken, although the government remains committed to sustainable fisheries and the discard ban, as set out in its manifesto commitments, and will promote international cooperation in the management of shared stocks.</p>","Camborne and Redruth","George Eustice",,"2016-09-08T10:32:18.077Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/576413/answer","Biography information for George Eustice","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/576413/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/576413/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2016-09-05","Fisheries","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, if she will make it her policy to ensure that UK fisheries are managed at or below maximum sustainable yield by 2020; what steps she plans to take to maintain a sustainable fisheries policy after the UK leaves the EU; and if she will take steps to work with European partners to support sustainable fishing after the UK leaves the EU.","false","Biography information for Kerry McCarthy","Bristol East","Kerry McCarthy","44902"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/576414","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2016-09-08","<p>The UK is committed to the development and implementation by the International Seabed Authority of a deep sea mining code in respect of areas outside national jurisdiction. A clear red line for the United Kingdom is that such a code, which is a prerequisite for the commencement of deep sea mining operations, ought to contain strong environmental protection. A first draft of a mining code was released by the International Seabed Authority in July 2016, and the UK will be submitting comments in due course.</p>","Reading West","Alok Sharma",,"2016-09-08T15:31:12.593Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/576414/answer","Biography information for Alok Sharma","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/576414/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/576414/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2016-09-05","Mining: Seas and Oceans","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what assessment his Department has made of the potential merits of putting in place a comprehensive system of environmental protection before deep sea mining operations are allowed to commence in oceans worldwide.","false","Biography information for Martyn Day","Linlithgow and East Falkirk","Martyn Day","44959"
