"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/573604","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2016-09-07","<p>We have maintained the protection provided by the statutory reasonable preference criteria which ensure that overall priority for allocation of social housing continues to be given to those in the greatest housing need. The reasonable preference categories include people who are homeless and those owed certain duties under the homelessness legislation.</p>","Nuneaton","Mr Marcus Jones",,"2016-09-07T15:23:34.687Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/573604/answer","Biography information for Mr Marcus Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/573604/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/573604/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2016-09-02","Homelessness: Social Rented Housing","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, what steps his Department is taking to require local authorities to prioritise homeless people in the allocation of social housing.","false","Biography information for Dan Jarvis","Barnsley Central","Dan Jarvis","44590"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/573605","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2016-09-07","<p>National planning policy is clear that in developing their local plans, planning authorities should consider the needs of a wide range of households, including older and disabled households.</p><p>The role of higher accessibility standards for new housing was considered during the Housing Standards Review undertaken by the Coalition Government. As a result, Optional Requirements for higher levels of accessibility were introduced into the Building Regulations and came into force on 1 October 2015. It was decided at that time that the application of these standards should remain a matter for Local Planning Authorities taking into account local needs and viability.</p><p>Details of relevant consultations and impact assessments can be found at the link below:</p><p>https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/2010-to-2015-government-policy-building-regulation/2010-to-2015-government-policy-building-regulation#appendix-5-technical-housing-standards-review</p>","Croydon Central","Gavin Barwell",,"2016-09-07T15:24:58.347Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/573605/answer","Biography information for Lord Barwell","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/573605/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/573605/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2016-09-02","Planning: Standards","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, what assessment he has made of the potential merits of making compulsory the accessibility standards outlined in the National Planning Policy Framework.","false","Biography information for Martyn Day","Linlithgow and East Falkirk","Martyn Day","44579"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/573606","Department for Culture, Media and Sport","true","2016-09-07","<p>The NCS Trust does not collect data at a constituency level. Therefore, the figures in the table below are for the local authority area of Swindon. Details of participation rates have been held at local authority level since 2012. The participation rates set out below also include a small number of participants from Northern Ireland.</p><p> </p><p>There was considerable national growth in the programme in 2015 – exact figures on 2015 NCS participation will be published in the independent evaluation in due course.</p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p><ins class="ministerial"><strong>Year</strong></ins></p></td><td><p><ins class="ministerial"><strong>Swindon</strong></ins></p></td><td><p><ins class="ministerial"><strong>England and Northern Ireland</strong></ins></p></td></tr><tr><td><p><ins class="ministerial">2011</ins></p></td><td><p><ins class="ministerial">-</ins></p></td><td><p><ins class="ministerial">8,434</ins></p></td></tr><tr><td><p><ins class="ministerial">2012</ins></p></td><td><p><ins class="ministerial">117</ins></p></td><td><p><ins class="ministerial">26,003</ins></p></td></tr><tr><td><p><ins class="ministerial">2013</ins></p></td><td><p><ins class="ministerial">110</ins></p></td><td><p><ins class="ministerial">39,994</ins></p></td></tr><tr><td><p><ins class="ministerial">2014</ins></p></td><td><p><ins class="ministerial">181</ins></p></td><td><p><ins class="ministerial">57,789</ins></p></td></tr></tbody></table><p><ins class="ministerial"> </ins></p><table><tbody><tr><td><p><del class="ministerial"><strong>Year</strong></del></p></td><td><p><del class="ministerial"><strong>Swindon</strong></del></p></td><td><p><del class="ministerial"><strong>England and Northern Ireland</strong></del></p></td></tr><tr><td><p><del class="ministerial">2011</del></p></td><td><p><del class="ministerial">-</del></p></td><td><p><del class="ministerial">8,434</del></p></td></tr><tr><td><p><del class="ministerial">2012</del></p></td><td><p><del class="ministerial">117</del></p></td><td><p><del class="ministerial">26,003</del></p></td></tr><tr><td><p><del class="ministerial">2013</del></p></td><td><p><del class="ministerial">110</del></p></td><td><p><del class="ministerial">39,994</del></p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p>","Reading East","Mr Rob Wilson",,"2016-09-07T15:54:29.083Z","2016-09-12T13:06:33.807Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/573606/answer","Biography information for Mr Rob Wilson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/573606/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/573606/answer","Reading East","Mr Rob Wilson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/573606/answer/previousversion/9630","Biography information for Mr Rob Wilson","10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2016-09-02","Voluntary Work: Young People","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, how many young people from (a) North Swindon and (b) England have participated in the National Citizen Service in each of the last five years.","false","Biography information for Justin Tomlinson","North Swindon","Justin Tomlinson","44588"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/573607","Department for Culture, Media and Sport","false","2016-09-12","<p>The Department for Exiting the European Union has responsibility for overseeing preparations for the withdrawal of the UK from the EU and conducting these withdrawal negotiations in support of the Prime Minister. In doing this it is working very closely with other government departments, including DCMS, and a wide range of other interested parties.</p>","West Suffolk","Matt Hancock",,"2016-09-12T12:46:49.19Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/573607/answer","Biography information for Matt Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/573607/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/573607/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2016-09-02","Department for Culture, Media and Sport: Brexit","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, what steps her Department has taken to prepare for the UK to leave the EU since 23 June 2016; and what further such steps her Department plans to take in the remainder of 2016.","false","Biography information for Karl McCartney","Lincoln","Karl McCartney","44244"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/573608","Department for Culture, Media and Sport","false","2016-09-12","<p>DCMS records show that there were no secondments to the Department from (a) PwC, (b) Deloitte, (c) Ernst and Young, (d) KPMG and (e) other consulting firms in the last three financial years.</p>","West Suffolk","Matt Hancock",,"2016-09-12T14:40:45.643Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/573608/answer","Biography information for Matt Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/573608/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/573608/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2016-09-02","Department for Culture, Media and Sport: Consultants","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, if she will publish a list of all secondees to her Department from (a) PwC, (b) Deloitte, (c) Ernst and Young, (d) KPMG and (e) other consulting firms in the last three financial years; and what the role was of each of those secondees.","false","Biography information for Dame Margaret Hodge","Barking","Margaret Hodge","44326"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/573609","Department for Culture, Media and Sport","false","2016-09-12","<p>DCMS has not used the services of (a) PwC, (b) Deloitte, (c) Ernst and Young, (d) KPMG and (e) other consulting firms in the last three financial years</p><p> </p>","West Suffolk","Matt Hancock",,"2016-09-12T14:41:24.4Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/573609/answer","Biography information for Matt Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/573609/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/573609/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2016-09-02","Department for Culture, Media and Sport: Consultants","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, how many times her Department has used the services of (a) PwC, (b) Deloitte, (c) Ernst and Young, (d) KPMG and (e) other consulting firms in the last three financial years; and what (i) work was undertaken and (ii) the cost to the public purse was on each such occasion.","false","Biography information for Dame Margaret Hodge","Barking","Margaret Hodge","44346"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/573610","Department for Culture, Media and Sport","false","2016-09-12","<p>The Government has accepted the case for airport expansion in the South East and the Airports' Commission's shortlisted options. The new Culture Secretary will be ensuring that tourism is one of the factors considered, when a final decision is taken on a preferred scheme.</p>","Chatham and Aylesford","Tracey Crouch","45279","2016-09-12T16:11:23.697Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/573610/answer","Biography information for Tracey Crouch","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/573610/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/573610/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2016-09-02","Heathrow Airport: Tourism","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, what discussion she has had with Cabinet colleagues on the effect of the possible expansion of Heathrow Airport on UK tourism.","false","Biography information for Jim Shannon","Strangford","Jim Shannon","44380"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/573611","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-09-12","<p>Detailed information about the work undertaken in individual contracts could only be provided at disproportionate cost. The table below shows the number of times the Ministry of Defence (MOD) has used the services of PwC, Deloitte, Ernst and Young and KPMG and the total expenditure for each financial year.</p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p>Vendor Name</p></td><td><p>Number of Contracts</p></td><td><p>2013-14 Payments</p></td><td><p>2014-15 Payments</p></td><td><p>2015-16 Payments</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>PRICEWATERHOUSECOOPERS LLP</p></td><td><p>20</p></td><td><p>£12,291,493</p></td><td><p>£10,495,047</p></td><td><p>£17,459,400</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>DELOITTE LLP</p></td><td><p>44</p></td><td><p>£22,239,558</p></td><td><p>£12,325,152</p></td><td><p>£12,342,592</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>DELOITTE MCS LIMITED</p></td><td><p>12</p></td><td><p>£6,142,266</p></td><td><p>£6,792,413</p></td><td><p>£2,675,673</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>ERNST &amp; YOUNG LLP</p></td><td><p>10</p></td><td><p>£17,258,841</p></td><td><p>£16,996,746</p></td><td><p>£18,786,874</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>KPMG LLP</p></td><td><p>24</p></td><td><p>£25,284,417</p></td><td><p>£38,350,698</p></td><td><p>£33,175,164</p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>Total</strong></p></td><td><p>110</p></td><td><p>£83,216,575</p></td><td><p>£84,960,056</p></td><td><p>£84,439,703</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><p> </p><p>Although the MOD can identify its direct expenditure with individual companies it does not specifically record centrally if the company is a consultancy firm. It is therefore not possible to identify (e) other consulting firms without being provided with a list of specific companies. Non-consulting companies can also provide consultancy services to the MOD as part of a larger contract.</p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin",,"2016-09-12T14:41:48.367Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/573611/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/573611/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/573611/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-09-02","Ministry of Defence: Consultants","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how many times his Department has used the services of (a) PwC, (b) Deloitte, (c) Ernst and Young, (d) KPMG and (e) other consulting firms in the last three financial years; and what (i) work was undertaken and (ii) the cost to the public purse was on each such occasion.","false","Biography information for Dame Margaret Hodge","Barking","Margaret Hodge","44347"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/573612","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-09-07","<p>The Ministry of Defence is currently examining options for the future of Defence Business Services (DBS) as part of the Future DBS Programme. No final decisions have been taken on whether any elements of DBS current operations will be outsourced. The scope of any potential Corporate Services Integration and Innovation Provider (CSIIP) contract will be confirmed in the event that a decision to outsource is taken.</p>","Milton Keynes North","Mark Lancaster",,"2016-09-07T14:48:35.693Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/573612/answer","Biography information for Mark Lancaster","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/573612/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/573612/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-09-02","Defence Business Services: Contracts","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what functions undertaken by Defence Business Services are being considered for inclusion in the Corporate Services Integration and Innovation Provider contract.","false","Biography information for Mary Glindon","North Tyneside","Mary Glindon","44386"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/573613","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-09-09","<p>Fewer than five employees from PwC, Deloitte, Ernst and Young, KPMG and other consulting firms were seconded to the Ministry of Defence within the last three years. Due to the low numbers involved, a breakdown of companies and job roles has not been provided.</p>","Milton Keynes North","Mark Lancaster",,"2016-09-09T12:47:28.307Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/573613/answer","Biography information for Mark Lancaster","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/573613/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/573613/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-09-02","Ministry of Defence: Consultants","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, if he will publish a list of all secondees to his Department from (a) PwC, (b) Deloitte, (c) Ernst and Young, (d) KPMG and (e) other consulting firms in the last three financial years; and what the role was of each of those secondees.","false","Biography information for Dame Margaret Hodge","Barking","Margaret Hodge","44327"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/573614","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-09-07","<p>No decision has been made on the future use of Bassingbourn Barracks. The site will be considered as part of the ongoing work of the Estate Optimisation Strategy which is due to report later this year.</p>","Milton Keynes North","Mark Lancaster",,"2016-09-07T14:29:16.763Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/573614/answer","Biography information for Mark Lancaster","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/573614/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/573614/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-09-02","Bassingbourn Barracks","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what progress his Department has made on the plans for the use of the Bassingbourn Barracks.","false","Biography information for Heidi Allen","South Cambridgeshire","Heidi Allen","44403"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/573615","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-09-12","<p>The Department for Exiting the EU has responsibility for overseeing preparations for the withdrawal of the UK from the EU and conducting these withdrawal negotiations in support of the Prime Minister. In doing this, it is working very closely with other Government departments, including the Ministry of Defence, and a wide range of other interested parties.</p>","Hemel Hempstead","Mike Penning",,"2016-09-12T14:50:54.27Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/573615/answer","Biography information for Sir Mike Penning","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/573615/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/573615/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-09-02","Ministry of Defence: Brexit","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what steps his Department has taken to prepare for the UK to leave the EU since 23 June 2016; and what further such steps his Department plans to take in the remainder of 2016.","false","Biography information for Karl McCartney","Lincoln","Karl McCartney","44245"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/573616","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-09-07","<p>Continuity of Education Allowance (CEA) was reviewed as part of the Strategic Defence and Security Review 2010. Since then, our reforms have reduced costs by around £30 million per annum along with an associated reduction in claimants. Work continues to further reduce the cost of the allowance, whilst ensuring funding goes to those who really need it, with the latest governance changes taking effect on 1 September 2016.</p><p> </p><p>The requested information is provided in the following table.</p><p> </p><p>Continuity of Education Allowance, Number of Claimants and Cost (UK and Overseas) by Financial Year (FY)</p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p> </p></td><td><p><strong>FY 2015-16</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p>UK Claimants</p></td><td><p>3,040</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Overseas Claimants</p></td><td><p>630</p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>Total Claimants</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>3,670</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p>UK Cost (£ million)</p></td><td><p>67</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Overseas Cost (£ million)</p></td><td><p>13.8</p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>Total Cost (£ million)</strong></p></td><td><p>80.8</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p>Note: all numbers are rounded</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","Milton Keynes North","Mark Lancaster","44196","2016-09-07T15:16:27.957Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/573616/answer","Biography information for Mark Lancaster","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/573616/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/573616/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-09-02","Armed Forces: Private Education","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how much was spent by his Department on private school fees for children whose parents are stationed (a) in the UK and (b) overseas in the last financial year.","false","Biography information for Rachel Reeves","Leeds West","Rachel Reeves","44194"
