"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/573618","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-09-08","<p>We review eligible locations every six months as standard but Ministers have no plans to change the qualifying criteria.</p>","Milton Keynes North","Mark Lancaster","45090","2016-09-08T13:57:40.99Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/573618/answer","Biography information for Mark Lancaster","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/573618/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/573618/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-09-02","Armed Forces: Pay","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what plans his Department has to review the eligibility for the operational allowance for service personnel.","false","Biography information for Brendan O'Hara","Argyll and Bute","Brendan O'Hara","44267"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/573619","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-09-09","<p>Every eligible applicant, irrespective of their background, residency or nationality undergoes appropriate security vetting as part of the selection process to join the UK Armed Forces.</p>","Milton Keynes North","Mark Lancaster",,"2016-09-09T12:59:29.257Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/573619/answer","Biography information for Mark Lancaster","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/573619/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/573619/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-09-02","Armed Forces: Northern Ireland","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, for what reasons people who are from or live in Northern Ireland are required to complete a counter terrorist check as part of an application to join the armed forces.","false","Biography information for Danny Kinahan","South Antrim","Danny Kinahan","44296"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/573620","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-09-08","<p>The Armed Forces Covenant is making a real difference in Northern Ireland, where it is enshrined in law. Funding bids have been more successful there than in any other part of the UK - grants include £450,000 to Combat Stress to provide mental health support to veterans.</p><p>There is an open invitation to the Northern Ireland Executive to join the Covenant Reference Group (CRG). The Government wishes them to take a full and active part in the group, alongside the other Devolved Administrations. Whilst the Northern Ireland Executive has not yet put forward a representative for the CRG, much useful and effective engagement takes place at Executive departmental level.</p>","Milton Keynes North","Mark Lancaster",,"2016-09-08T14:01:13.1Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/573620/answer","Biography information for Mark Lancaster","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/573620/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/573620/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-09-02","Armed Forces Covenant Reference Group: Northern Ireland","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what recent discussions he has had with the Northern Ireland Executive on the appointment of a representative from Northern Ireland to the Armed Forces Covenant Reference Group.","false","Biography information for Danny Kinahan","South Antrim","Danny Kinahan","44297"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/573621","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-09-12","<p>Between November 2014 and the end of August 2016 there have been 473 Hellfire missiles used in Iraq and Syria as part of Operation SHADER. The estimated cost of the use of these missiles is £44.455 million.</p>","Hemel Hempstead","Mike Penning",,"2016-09-12T14:56:13.013Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/573621/answer","Biography information for Sir Mike Penning","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/573621/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/573621/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-09-02","Islamic State: Military Intervention","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how many Hellfire missiles have been used in Syria and Iraq to date as part of Operation SHADER; and what the cost of the use of those weapons has been to the public purse.","false","Biography information for Alison Thewliss","Glasgow Central","Alison Thewliss","44289"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/573622","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-09-07","<p>I refer the hon. Member to the answer my predecessor (Philip Dunne) gave on 27 June 2016 to Question 905474 to the hon. Member for Rutherglen and Hamilton West (Margaret Ferrier).</p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin",,"2016-09-07T14:29:52.08Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/573622/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/573622/answer","Hansard Extract 27 June 2016 HOC 509474.docx","Type 26 Frigates","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/573622/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-09-02","Type 26 Frigates","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, if he will make an assessment of the effect of changes to the timetable in the procurement of Type 26 Frigates on (a) jobs, (b) apprenticeships and (c) skills in the affected shipyards in the next six months.","false","Biography information for Chris Stephens","Glasgow South West","Chris Stephens","44582"
